Some less flammable plant alternatives for close landscaping include Columbine, lavender, Coreopsis and Geranium. You can also plant alternative trees and shrubs further from the house. Some good options include buckthorn, lilac, maple and birch. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/40/Prepare-for-a-Forest-Fire-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Prepare-for-a-Forest-Fire-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/40/Prepare-for-a-Forest-Fire-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Prepare-for-a-Forest-Fire-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
